Linkage Assurance Plc has expressed its commitment to Corporate Social Responsibility. The company said in a statement that it donated uniform kits to Lagos Metropolitan Area Transport Authority for the use of its highway managers working on the declared road networks across Lagos State. At the presentation ceremony, which was held at the LAMATA office, the Managing Director/Chief Executive Officer, Linkage Assurance, Mr Daniel Braie, commended LAMATA for various transformational projects the organisation had executed in transport infrastructure since its inception. He commended the agency for its achievement under the current Managing Director, Mrs Abimbola Akinajo. He said Linkage Assurance was prepared to forge a greater strategic alliance with LAMATA in order to actualise its CSR objectives in Lagos State. Braie also explained that as part of its CSR projects, Linkage Assurance had always been committed to improving the standard of living of Nigerians by making the environment safe and more liveable. The statement said apart from extending sponsorships to the Down Syndrome Foundation and Children Living with Cancer Foundation recently, the company had equally engaged in other events and forms of support such as supporting government efforts to contain COVID-19 pandemic by the Nigerian insurance industry. Akinajo expressed her appreciation to Linkage Assurance for the donation and expressed LAMATAâ€™s willingness to collaborate with the organisation, the statement said.